{"id":932,"category_slug":"ielts-listening","category_name":"IELTS Listening","position":285,"title":"Cam3 - Test 4 - Part 1","subtitle":"Susan’s Baby Announcement","level":"B1","parts":74,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/ielts-listening/cam3-test-4-part-1.932/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/0-ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1.mp3","transcript":"John, I've just had some good news.\nSusan has had her baby.\nDo you know when she had it?\nYesterday.\nThe 10th of August.\nOh, my father was born on August the 10th.\nGive me the details and I'll make a note for everyone at work.\nOkay.\nWell, was it a boy or a girl?\nIt's a boy.\nAnd what are they going to call him?\nTom.\nTom Lightfoot.\nIt sounds quite good, don't you think?\nYes, that has quite a good ring to it.\nYou know he's quite a big baby.\nHe weighed 4.25 kilos when he was born.\nThat does sound big, 4.25 kilos.\nAnd he's long too, 46 centimetres.\nMmmm. Tall parents.\nHe'll grow up to be over 2 metres, I'd say.\nWith masses of black hair, curly black hair.\nYou know, we should go and visit them in hospital.\nWhat about tomorrow afternoon at around 1 pm?\nYes, okay.\nWhere should we meet?...\nAh, I could come and pick you up at your house, if you like.\nYes, that would be wonderful.\nMy car is still off the road.\nJust refresh my memory....\nWhat's the address again?\nIt's 15 Chesterfield Road, Paddington.\nIt's next to the library, isn't it?\nNot exactly. It's next to a bank.\nThe State Bank actually.\nThe library is opposite us, on the corner.\nThat's right,\nand there's a garage on the other street corner. I remember now.\nSo, you'll pick me up at 12.45\nand we'll be there at one easily.\nNow what should we take?\nWe must take them something.\nI always think flowers are good to take to someone in hospital, don't you?\nWell, not really.\nEveryone always brings flowers and they don't last.\nI think it's much better to take a pot plant,\nso she can take it home with her.\nYes, but then she has to remember to water it.\nWhat about a big box of chocolates?\nOkay, chocolates sound fine.\nWe should get something for the baby too. What do you think?\nYes, you're right.\nWhat do you think of something like baby shampoo or talcum powder?\nOr we could get a little hat, or something like that.\nWe don't know the size, or the right colour, do we?\nI think we should get something they wouldn't normally buy.\nWhat about a soft toy of some sort?\nYes, a soft toy.\nWhat about a teddy bear?\nI could get one early tomorrow at the market\nand I could probably get the chocolates there too.\nGood.\nSo you'll pick me up at a quarter to one at my place\nand I'll make sure that I've got the presents.\nYou must remember how much you paid for the gifts,\nso I can pay you back for half.\nIf they're going to be from both of us, I would like to go shares.\nOkay.\nI'd say the chocolates would be about $15 for something nice and not too small\nand the toy would be around $35 or so, I'd think.\nGood, that'll be fine. About $25 each then.\nGood, I'll pick you up then on Sunday at 12.45.\nOkay.\nSee you then. Bye.","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:51:59","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"John, I've just had some good news.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/1.mp3","time_start":0.2,"time_end":2.95},{"position":2,"content":"Susan has had her baby.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/2.mp3","time_start":2.95,"time_end":4.82},{"position":3,"content":"Do you know when she had it?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/3.mp3","time_start":5.03,"time_end":6.51},{"position":4,"content":"Yesterday.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/4.mp3","time_start":6.51,"time_end":7.6},{"position":5,"content":"The 10th of August.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/5.mp3","time_start":7.6,"time_end":9.16},{"position":6,"content":"Oh, my father was born on August the 10th.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/6.mp3","time_start":9.16,"time_end":12.7},{"position":7,"content":"Give me the details and I'll make a note for everyone at work.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/7.mp3","time_start":13.19,"time_end":16.09},{"position":8,"content":"Okay.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/8.mp3","time_start":16.09,"time_end":17.22},{"position":9,"content":"Well, was it a boy or a girl?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/9.mp3","time_start":17.61,"time_end":19.99},{"position":10,"content":"It's a boy.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/10.mp3","time_start":19.99,"time_end":21.27},{"position":11,"content":"And what are they going to call him?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/11.mp3","time_start":21.27,"time_end":23.2},{"position":12,"content":"Tom.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/12.mp3","time_start":23.49,"time_end":24.36},{"position":13,"content":"Tom Lightfoot.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/13.mp3","time_start":24.36,"time_end":25.64},{"position":14,"content":"It sounds quite good, don't you think?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/14.mp3","time_start":25.64,"time_end":27.4},{"position":15,"content":"Yes, that has quite a good ring to it.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/15.mp3","time_start":27.4,"time_end":30.19},{"position":16,"content":"You know he's quite a big baby.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/16.mp3","time_start":30.19,"time_end":32.92},{"position":17,"content":"He weighed 4.25 kilos when he was born.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/17.mp3","time_start":33.19,"time_end":36.31},{"position":18,"content":"That does sound big, 4.25 kilos.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/18.mp3","time_start":37.06,"time_end":39.93},{"position":19,"content":"And he's long too, 46 centimetres.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/19.mp3","time_start":39.93,"time_end":43.19},{"position":20,"content":"Mmmm. Tall parents.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/20.mp3","time_start":43.19,"time_end":45.83},{"position":21,"content":"He'll grow up to be over 2 metres, I'd say.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/21.mp3","time_start":45.97,"time_end":48.58},{"position":22,"content":"With masses of black hair, curly black hair.","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/ielts-listening/ielts-cambridge-3-test-4-part-1-2023-08-20-18-52-26/22.mp3","time_start":48.58,"